{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, we define 5-class general responses to express Yes, No, Maybe, Question, and Stop (e.g., \"Yes\", \"I don't know\", \"Stop\", \"Maybe\", and \"I don't understand your question\") as well as a mapping table between the Scores and general responses for each dimension.",
    "For example, the Score of \"Yes\" is 0 to the question \"Are you showing up for work or school?\"",
    "in Managing Work/School, while it is 2 to the question \"Do you often drink alone?\"",
    "in Alcohol Abuse.Since CaiTI asks open-ended questions, user responses are infinitely diverse (YES/NO answers or open-ended responses).",
    "With a Score of 2, CaiTI will conduct the psychotherapeutic conversational intervention."
  ]
}